entry.title: Putin Uses Russia's Victory Day Parade to Justify Invasion of Ukraine
entry.content: Speaking in Red Square during the annual commemoration of Russia’s victory in World War II, the Kremlin leader said Russia was under threat when it decided to take pre-emptive action in its neighboring country.

entry.title: From Tycoons to Pop Singers, Ukrainians of All Walks Come Together on the Front Lines
entry.content: A farming entrepreneur and a pop star are among Ukraine’s Territorial Defense forces, who, steeled in battle, are trying to make up with motivation what they lack in experience.

entry.title: Philippines Votes for President With Ex-Dictator's Son Leading Opinion Polls
entry.content: Ferdinand Marcos Jr. is seeking the country’s top political job more than 3½ decades after his father was deposed in 1986.

entry.title: Desperate to Cross Into the U.S., Some Brazilians Create Phony Families
entry.content: The illegal arrangements allow some Brazilian migrants to get a green light from Border Patrol and start new lives.
